==English==

===Etymology===
From sal ammoniac, which was first obtained near the temple of Jupiter in [[w:Ammon|Ammon]], by burning camel's dung.  See [[Ammoniac]].

===Pronunciation===
*[[WEAE]] {{IPA|/ʌˈmon.jʌ/}}

===Noun===
'''ammonia'''

# {{chemistry}} A gaseous compound of [[hydrogen]] and [[nitrogen]], NH<sub>3</sub>, with a pungent smell and taste.  Obsolete names include [[volatile alkali]], and [[spirits of hartshorn]].

